{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T03:37:37.328Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Generalization"},{"type":"text","text":" in supervised learning is a model's ability to make accurate predictions on "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"new, unseen data"},{"type":"text","text":" (not just the training data it memorized). It is the ultimate goal of machine learning: capturing true underlying patterns rather than noise."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Definition"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"$\\text{Generalization} = \\text{Performance on unseen data from the same distribution as training data}"}},{"type":"text","text":"$"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A model that generalizes well has low "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"generalization error"},{"type":"text","text":" (also called test error), meaning it performs well on data it hasn't encountered during training."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Generalization Matters"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"In supervised learning (regression & classification), we train on labeled data but deploy in real-world scenarios with new inputs:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Scenario"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Training Data"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Test"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Regression"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., house price prediction)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Historical prices of 10,000 houses"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Predict price for a new house"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Classification"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., spam detector)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"50,000 labeled emails (spam/not-spam)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Classify incoming emails"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Without generalization, a model is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"practically useless"},{"type":"text","text":"—it only works on data it already saw."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Two Failure Modes"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Overfitting"},{"type":"text","text":" (Too Complex)"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":